ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class Resume

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.Resume
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Resume
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Restarts the playing or recording of a previously suspended message at its current position.

    The Record request has these parameters:

    Resume Request Parameters
    connection Required Specifies the device on which the message is to be resumed (only the deviceID field of the connectionID is used).
    messageToResume Not supported
    duration Not supported
    extensions Not supported

    The following events are generated as a result of this service:

    • PlayEvent
    • RecordEvent

    CSTA Functional Requirements have been implemented as follows:

    • CSTA Reposition service is not yet supported, therefore the position pointer can not be manipulated.

    Refer to ECMA-269, Figure 6-21, "Voice Unit Operational Model" in section 6.2.1 for the operational model.

    Negative Acknowledgements:

    • operation:invalidParameterValue - Sent if an invalid parameter is passed.
    • operation:invalidConnectionID - Sent if unable to find the Media Session associated with the DeviceID of this request.
    • operation:invalidMsgID - Sent if the specified messageID is invalid or if the File (messageID) is not found.
    • operation:messageIDRequired - Sent if messageID is null.
    • operation:generic - Sent if an IOError occurred or if a channel is already closed.
    • systemResourceAvailability:generic - Sent if a severe system error like un-availability of a system wide resource.
    • stateIncompatibility:invalidObjectState - Sent if the player or recorder is in an invalid state.
    • unspecified - Sent if an implementation-specific error occurs.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
    See Also:
